{
  "texts": [
    "By critically examining the limitations of current approaches and drawing on the latest research in model architecture, data fusion, and training methodologies, we seek to chart a path forward that could significantly improve the model's ability to process, understand, and generate multimodal content.",
    "This effort not only contributes to the theoretical foundations of multimodal AI but also paves the way for practical advancements in AI applications, heralding a new era of more capable, intuitive, and human-like AI systems.",
    "This section reviews previous efforts in multimodal large language models (LLMs), focusing on their limitations and the gap this work aims to fill.",
    "Data Fusion Techniques in AIVarious methodologies have been explored for combining data from different modalities such as text, images, and audio.It was found that early fusion techniques, which combine data at the input level, could enhance feature integration, but were often limited by the homogeneity in feature space [10]- [12].",
    "Late fusion techniques, which combine data at the decision level, offered flexibility but sometimes failed to capture intermodal interactions effectively [13], [14]."
  ]
}